1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:01,940
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,940 --> 00:00:03,210
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,210 --> 00:00:04,910
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:07,610
Ms. Choi's back?

5
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:10,220
The chairman gave the order himself.

6
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,720
If that's the case...

7
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,120
She definitely wasn't bluffing
about Temi Bio.

8
00:00:15,550 --> 00:00:16,620
So what are you going to do now?

9
00:00:17,020 --> 00:00:20,730
I'm going to find out what secret
she knows about Temi Bio.

10
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:24,130
And I'll make Oh Jung Ran pay
for what she did to me.

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,470
After getting kicked out,
you made a flashy comeback...

12
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:35,970
and boldly claimed the chairman is
on your side.

13
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:39,240
That tells me you have dirt
on Chairman Park.

14
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,280
But...

15
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,920
how long do you think
he'll put up with it?

16
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:52,590
We're talking
about Chairman Park of Adele.

17
00:00:54,030 --> 00:00:55,590
Can you really handle him
on your own?

18
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,660
What are you talking about?

19
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,710
How about we...

20
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,770
be friends?

21
00:01:11,710 --> 00:01:15,350
I'll help you use
the leverage you have...

22
00:01:16,350 --> 00:01:18,420
to your advantage.

23
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:32,130
And you are?

24
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:43,510
I'm Kim Myung Hui,
the president of the Adele Group.

25
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:47,350
I'm here to propose a deal, sir.

26
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:52,380
The dirt you have on Chairman Park
is a double-edged sword.

27
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:57,690
You can use it to control him,
but it's just as dangerous for you.

28
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:01,390
I'll help you so you can stand up...

29
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:03,460
to him.

30
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:05,860
But in return...

31
00:02:06,970 --> 00:02:08,100
In return?

32
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:12,000
Just this once, use your leverage
on Chairman Park Tae Ho...

33
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:14,310
for me.

34
00:02:15,070 --> 00:02:16,070
What?

35
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:19,010
You know my dad, right?

36
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:22,980
Officially, he's an investment pro,
but his real specialty...

37
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:26,720
is M and A.

38
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:29,620
In other words, a corporate raider.

39
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:31,620
We want...

40
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:35,730
to acquire Adele Group's bio division
at a good price.

41
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:39,100
Don't tell me...

42
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:42,370
Was that your plan all along
when you came to Adele?

43
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:45,800
Good. That's exactly
what I want you to think.

44
00:02:46,770 --> 00:02:50,140
I'm tired of always building up
other people's companies.

45
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:55,650
Now, I want my own company
so I can run my business my way.

46
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:58,650
And Adele Group's bio division...

47
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:01,720
is quite appealing.

48
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:03,390
Still,

49
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:06,260
I stole your design book.

50
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:08,560
And yet,
you suddenly want to be friends?

51
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:10,900
You want us to team up?

52
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:14,070
Emotions are a luxury in business.

53
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:19,600
Petty emotional fights come second
to my goals and profits.

54
00:03:20,610 --> 00:03:24,280
You seem like someone
who gets what I'm talking about.

55
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:26,540
Am I wrong?

56
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,720
That's right, Choi Yu Na.

57
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,950
Take the hand I'm offering you.

58
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:41,060
I'll help you rattle
Chairman Park Tae Ho's cage.

59
00:03:42,260 --> 00:03:46,660
And bit by bit,
I'll push you to the cliff's edge,

60
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,030
right into the path
of Chairman Park's cruel blade.

61
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,740
And then I'll give you
a nice, hard shove.

62
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:03,010
So, you're President Kim Myung Hui
of the Adele Group,

63
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:06,480
and you want to do business
with Eunhwa Trading?

64
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:09,620
What specifically
did you want to trade?

65
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,630
I'm not here for goods.
I'm here for secrets.

66
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,060
Why don't we start...

67
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:19,330
with the secret
behind this painting?

68
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:26,140
You've always been a fan
of the artist Seo Yi Bon's work,

69
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:27,710
and in 2019,

70
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:31,140
you received a piece
from Chairman Park's collection...

71
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:32,880
through the Adele Gallery...

72
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,910
as a bribe.

73
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,520
What are you talking about?

74
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,320
Did you know...

75
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,720
there's a ledger
documenting the bribe?

76
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:45,460
A ledger? What...

77
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:47,660
I've seen it myself.

78
00:04:48,290 --> 00:04:50,830
How else would I know?

79
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,630
As long as that ledger exists,

80
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,870
it'll cause you problems eventually.

81
00:04:57,970 --> 00:05:00,040
If you want it gone,

82
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:02,210
you'll have to make a deal with me.

83
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:09,250
What exactly is the deal
you're proposing?

84
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,850
I need one lie...

85
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:16,450
and one truth.

86
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,230
What's there to think about?

87
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,900
I didn't think you'd be this scared.

88
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,870
It's because I can't trust you.

89
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:38,310
Who makes deals based on trust?

90
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,650
You do it
if you stand to profit from it.

91
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:44,950
I'll give you some time.

92
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:47,290
Think about what you have to gain,

93
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:49,650
and nothing else.

94
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:54,860
And one more thing.

95
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,730
When you see Chairman Park,

96
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:03,530
tell him that leverage is now
in someone else's hands.

97
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:08,140
That if anything happens to you,
it'll all be made public.

98
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:10,210
Only then...

99
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:14,180
will your life be safe.

100
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,320
What was that?

101
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,890
How could she have guessed?

102
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:32,900
It's like she knew
the chairman had threatened...

103
00:06:33,630 --> 00:06:35,030
to kill me.

104
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:46,180
Chloe.

105
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:50,880
What were you and Choi Yu Na
talking about?

106
00:06:51,150 --> 00:06:52,220
She's claiming innocence?

107
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:54,290
You can't be buying
such a shameless lie.

108
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:56,990
If you can't accept this,
just say the word.

109
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,460
If you want,

110
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:02,090
I'll help you change
the chairman's mind.

111
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:10,770
He's the one who'll have it hardest
now that Choi Yu Na is back.

112
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:15,510
And he's worried about me?

113
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,590
You don't need to worry about me.

114
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:32,790
I just don't want to fight
about this anymore.

115
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:38,330
And if you two really want
to help me,

116
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:41,430
let's just pretend
the other day never happened.

117
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:45,740
I don't like being in the middle
of you two like this.

118
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,920
Stay out of Chloe's business.

119
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,220
That's enough.

120
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,060
I don't want to fight.

121
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:10,730
Sure.

122
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:13,660
If you want to pick a fight, make it
with Choi Yu Na or the chairman.

123
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,700
That's right.

124
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,000
Now that Choi Yu Na is back,

125
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:20,540
your wedding will be back on, right?

126
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:24,710
Stop worrying about Chloe
and mind your own business.

127
00:08:51,870 --> 00:08:52,870
Welcome...

128
00:08:58,780 --> 00:08:59,780
What do you want?

129
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,810
I'm here to meet someone.

130
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:04,180
Is it my sister?

131
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:09,720
Like I said before,
I'm totally against you two.

132
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:13,360
That's not why I'm here.

133
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,490
Wait, hold on a second.

134
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:20,260
Why are you so against it?
What's your problem with me?

135
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:23,030
Why are you getting so defensive?

136
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:26,840
You're not obsessed
with my sister, are you?

137
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,510
Obsessed?

138
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:31,410
No way. I told you, that's not it.

139
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:35,010
Anyway, you're definitely
not right for her.

140
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:37,880
Father.

141
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,090
Right.

142
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:45,620
It was him I was planning to meet,
not your sister.

143
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,790
Still...

144
00:09:47,890 --> 00:09:50,330
Still, you're really not right
for her!

145
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:52,400
- Never!
- Oh my gosh.

146
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,870
I said I wasn't interested. Never!

147
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,770
You confessed your feelings?

148
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:07,110
Yes. It just kind of happened.

149
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,550
I expressed my feelings for her.

150
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:13,520
I want to ask her out properly
and start a serious relationship.

151
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:16,950
I was hoping
for your blessing, Father.

152
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:22,190
Oh, dear.

153
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:26,200
Why do you even need my blessing?

154
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:29,530
What's most important
is Chloe's feelings.

155
00:10:30,370 --> 00:10:31,470
In that case,

156
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,670
could you give me some advice
on how to win her over?

157
00:10:35,370 --> 00:10:37,540
What does she like?

158
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:41,180
Jewelry? Flowers? Designer purses?

159
00:10:43,950 --> 00:10:47,550
No, Chloe's not really
into things like that.

160
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,760
She values things...

161
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:53,590
like sincerity, thoughtfulness,

162
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:57,530
and shared memories.
Things you can't really measure.

163
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,470
Sincerity, thoughtfulness,

164
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,530
and memories?

165
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:08,370
Memories?

166
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:10,710
He likes Jin Ju, too?

167
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:15,210
He's the son of her sworn enemy,
Chairman Park Tae Ho.

168
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,350
What am I going to do?

169
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,220
Memories?

170
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:29,530
Sincerity, thoughtfulness,
and memories.

171
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:33,430
Getting her a gift is harder
than I thought.

172
00:11:34,970 --> 00:11:36,570
She really is one of a kind.

173
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,040
Hang on.

174
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,470
A gift centered on memories
might be doable.

175
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,150
What's this about?

176
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,180
I just wanted to ask you something.

177
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:52,880
What college did you attend?

178
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:56,050
The Helion School of Design
in New York.

179
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,960
I also attended
the Avendia Business School.

180
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:01,830
But why the sudden interest
in my schools?

181
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:06,230
Come on, you know
how interested I am in you.

182
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:09,770
I told you, I don't want things
to get awkward.

183
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:11,200
That kind of attention...

184
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:14,640
Okay, message received.

185
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:17,640
But if you ever need my attention,
just say the word.

186
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:20,950
I've got attention, thoughtfulness,
sincerity, and memories...

187
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,050
to offer.

188
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:39,030
I guess that audio file I sent
really got under your skin.

189
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:41,330
You reinstated me in just one day.

190
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:45,000
If you keep acting arrogantly...

191
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,870
What's the worst you can do,
kill me?

192
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:52,280
After getting kicked out
and losing it all,

193
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,110
I realized something.

194
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,750
If I want to protect what's mine,

195
00:12:58,050 --> 00:13:00,250
I have to fight
like my life depends on it.

196
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:06,020
I won't stand here...

197
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,930
trembling before you anymore, sir.

198
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:11,500
Good.

199
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:14,730
If you're that determined,

200
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:18,800
that makes this much easier for me.

201
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:29,010
When you see Chairman Park,

202
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:32,820
tell him that leverage is now
in someone else's hands.

203
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:37,620
That if anything happens to you,
it'll all be made public.

204
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:39,660
Only then...

205
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:43,760
will your life be safe.

206
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:51,070
Don't think killing me
will be the end of it.

207
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:54,340
If I die, that recorded evidence...

208
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:57,110
will be released by someone else.

209
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,740
And now you're threatening me?

210
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:02,350
Let's call it a concern.

211
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:04,320
If something happens to me,

212
00:14:04,380 --> 00:14:06,650
you'll have a lot more
to answer for.

213
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,690
I'm just letting you know.

214
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:11,660
Your concern is much appreciated.

215
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:18,060
Then I'll assume
the wedding is back on.

216
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:25,100
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

217
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:36,050
What are your orders
regarding Ms. Choi?

218
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,620
Let her run wild for now.

219
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:42,050
Wait for an opportunity.

220
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,890
Once we retrieve
the recording device,

221
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:46,890
you'll take care of her.

222
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:49,930
Just like always,

223
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:51,660
make it clean.

224
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,730
Yes, sir.

225
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:05,080
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

226
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:06,580
(Eunhwa Trading)

227
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:20,090
What's this?

228
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:23,990
Did it actually work
the way Chloe said it would?

229
00:15:26,130 --> 00:15:28,500
Does teaming up with Chloe mean...

230
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:31,870
I can really do anything?

231
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:43,450
If you're here to ask him
to cancel my reinstatement,

232
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:44,950
don't bother.

233
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:48,920
He even said
the wedding was back on.

234
00:15:52,390 --> 00:15:53,420
Let's...

235
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,390
forget the past...

236
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,400
and start over, okay?

237
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:11,610
What you did, how you got back,

238
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,340
I don't care.

239
00:16:14,110 --> 00:16:16,410
No matter
how my father threatens me,

240
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,650
I have no intention...

241
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:22,820
of being with you.

242
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:28,460
Then who would you rather be with?

243
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:31,860
Are you going to waste your life
pining for the dead Baek Jin Ju?

244
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:35,830
Or will you latch onto Chloe,
her look-alike?

245
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:43,140
What?

246
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,240
Don't tell me...

247
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:48,510
you actually have feelings
for Chloe.

248
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:51,220
That's none of your business.

249
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,350
Chloe, of all people?

250
00:16:58,690 --> 00:16:59,690
Is that so?

251
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:04,190
If that's how you feel,
I'll have to change my plans.

252
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,070
You'll see.

253
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,830
In the end,

254
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,600
you'll be with me.

255
00:17:26,450 --> 00:17:29,250
- Father...
- Bring Oh Jung Ran to me!

256
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,970
What brings you all the way
to my office?

257
00:17:51,010 --> 00:17:53,780
You keep avoiding me.
What choice did I have?

258
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:55,550
You...

259
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,650
That thieving girl is
out of the question.

260
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,350
Don't tell me you came here
to see Chloe.

261
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:02,990
Say one more nasty thing to Chloe.
I swear,

262
00:18:03,790 --> 00:18:05,060
I won't let it slide.

263
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:10,090
Son,

264
00:18:10,530 --> 00:18:14,030
you're going to marry
whoever I choose for you anyway.

265
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:17,630
Why waste your energy on something
as pointless as love?

266
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:20,140
I won't agree
to a loveless marriage.

267
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,070
If you don't want
to lose your only son,

268
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:25,480
you need to let this go, Mom.

269
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:28,850
You're serious about her...

270
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:31,350
when she isn't.

271
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:35,250
What do you lack...

272
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:37,690
that you have to grovel and beg
for her affection?

273
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,630
Do you realize
how much this will hurt...

274
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:43,460
when your heart breaks?

275
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,530
You shouldn't even start
down that path.

276
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:51,470
In case you haven't noticed,

277
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:54,870
I already have.

278
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:59,280
Hey... Park Hyun Jun!

279
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,910
You've got to be kidding me.

280
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:06,480
Daughters may end up
like their moms,

281
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,350
but he should be different.

282
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:12,990
Why does he have to pine for someone
who doesn't love him back, like me?

283
00:19:13,060 --> 00:19:15,760
Jung Ran!

284
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,260
Chairman Park is looking for you.

285
00:19:20,630 --> 00:19:23,030
Manager Kang said things are bad.

286
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:25,400
What trouble have you caused
this time?

287
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:29,340
Trouble?
I haven't had time to cause any.

288
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:32,880
I don't know. He said to come home,
so you'd better hurry.

289
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:36,250
Wait, is it really safe to go home?

290
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:39,150
Shouldn't you be making
a run for it?

291
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:42,220
Run away? After finally
getting back into the house?

292
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:48,330
Let's go. I'm not afraid of him.

293
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:03,810
What are you doing here?

294
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:05,840
Why are you home at this hour?

295
00:20:06,710 --> 00:20:09,050
I wasn't feeling well,
so I left work early.

296
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:11,580
The chairman also came home early.

297
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:15,120
Please go into the study.

298
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:17,450
The chairman is waiting for you.

299
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,770
Jung Ran!

300
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:39,210
Honey.

301
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:44,480
Here's a little lie
from Eunhwa Trading.

302
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:46,280
Oh Jung Ran.

303
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:50,090
Call it payback for the humiliation
you put me through.

304
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:02,900
How dare you go behind my back...

305
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:06,040
and do something
that could be used against me?

306
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:13,780
What do you mean?
What did I do to deserve this?

307
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:22,090
You went to Eunhwa Trading
and strong-armed them.

308
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:24,820
What, Eunhwa Trading?

309
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,020
That bribery ledger you have.

310
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:31,190
Since that alone couldn't
bring me down,

311
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:36,270
you pushed them to claim
I gave the painting myself,

312
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,940
and you were just the messenger.

313
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:43,870
What do you mean?
I don't know anything about that.

314
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:45,380
Don't even think about denying it.

315
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:49,110
The CEO of Eunhwa Trading
told me himself.

316
00:21:54,890 --> 00:21:55,890
Kim Myung Hui.

317
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:58,690
Yes, it was her doing.

318
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:03,130
She's trying to get back at me,
so she set me up.

319
00:22:03,230 --> 00:22:06,000
How would she know anything
about Eunhwa Trading?

320
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:09,200
And why would
Eunhwa Trading's CEO lie?

321
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,100
At home and in public,

322
00:22:13,570 --> 00:22:15,310
everyone's trying to get leverage
on me.

323
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:18,040
How dare you all look down
on Park Tae Ho?

324
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:22,180
It wasn't me.
Kim Myung Hui set this all up.

325
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:25,450
She must've secretly
read my ledger and...

326
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,350
Enough with the pathetic excuses!

327
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:30,790
Get out and move to the annex.

328
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:32,990
Hand over the ledger.

329
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:36,130
You're done with the gallery, too.

330
00:22:36,660 --> 00:22:39,000
Please, honey.
You have to believe me.

331
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,330
It's not true, honey.

332
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:42,470
Let go of me!

333
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:45,600
Honey!

334
00:23:02,290 --> 00:23:03,290
Kim Myung Hui.

335
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:05,690
It was you, wasn't it?

336
00:23:05,990 --> 00:23:07,360
You orchestrated this whole thing.

337
00:23:08,860 --> 00:23:10,130
What now?

338
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:13,730
You knew all about
the bribery ledger.

339
00:23:14,260 --> 00:23:16,970
You used Eunhwa Trading
to frame me, didn't you?

340
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:20,200
The bribery ledger? Eunhwa Trading?

341
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:23,440
Enough. Quiet down! Let go of her.

342
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:25,940
Geun Tae, drag her to the annex.

343
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:27,610
What?

344
00:23:27,610 --> 00:23:29,710
Do you want to be thrown out again?

345
00:23:31,450 --> 00:23:32,450
No, sir.

346
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:41,760
Let's go, Jung Ran.

347
00:23:42,690 --> 00:23:44,190
Let's get you treated
at the annex first.

348
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:47,400
Let go of me.
Why am I the one getting kicked out?

349
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:49,800
I've been framed!

350
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:51,540
You're bleeding!

351
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:58,140
Let's go before you get hurt
even more. Come on.

352
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:03,780
You won't get away with this.
I'll find a way to expose you!

353
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:05,320
Let go!

354
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:13,460
Why is she taking it out on me?

355
00:24:14,830 --> 00:24:16,190
And what's Eunhwa Trading?

356
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:22,770
There's just a little trouble
with the gallery.

357
00:24:23,730 --> 00:24:24,840
You don't need to worry about it.

358
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:29,170
She couldn't have come across
Eunhwa Trading...

359
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:31,810
while looking into Temi Bio,
could she?

360
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:37,280
And one truth from Eunhwa Trading.

361
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,380
(Eunhwa Trading)

362
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:41,590
The person...

363
00:24:42,650 --> 00:24:44,420
who gave you this painting.

364
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:47,320
Was it Oh Jung Ran?

365
00:24:48,990 --> 00:24:49,990
No, it wasn't.

366
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,560
I dealt directly
with Chairman Park Tae Ho.

367
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,870
What kind of deal was it?

368
00:24:56,230 --> 00:24:58,200
I simply procured the item
he wanted.

369
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:02,470
That's all I can tell you.

370
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:04,570
Temi Bio.

371
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:08,550
A suspicious transaction
before Dr. Baek's accident.

372
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:10,410
And...

373
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:17,290
By the way,
why did you bring back Ms. Choi?

374
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:24,330
After the false accusation case
was resolved cleanly,

375
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:28,430
I assumed she'd learned her lesson
and allowed her back.

376
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,370
Besides,

377
00:25:31,870 --> 00:25:34,170
I couldn't risk her talking
about the kidnapping.

378
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,110
I see.

379
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:40,640
There's also Ms. Choi,
who leveraged...

380
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,050
what she knew about Temi Bio
to get reinstated.

381
00:25:43,580 --> 00:25:44,580
Temi Bio...

382
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:48,690
So it wasn't Oh Jung Ran
who hurt Dr. Baek,

383
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:52,220
but you, Park Tae Ho.

384
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:33,000
I'll accept your offer.

385
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:38,840
But you need to leave
Adele Group right now.

386
00:26:41,140 --> 00:26:42,140
Why would I do that?

387
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:45,710
Why do you think
I stole your design book?

388
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:49,350
It's because you're interfering
with my wedding.

389
00:26:49,510 --> 00:26:51,780
You're tempting Min Jun
with that face of yours.

390
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,750
If you're going to use
the chairman's weakness...

391
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:56,850
to buy the bio division,

392
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,820
then leave Adele Group right now.

393
00:27:02,190 --> 00:27:03,190
I don't know about that.

394
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:07,630
If I were you, I wouldn't make
leaving the company a condition.

395
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:10,270
If I leave the company,

396
00:27:10,270 --> 00:27:13,140
it'll be harder
to fight Chairman Park.

397
00:27:13,970 --> 00:27:15,210
And I could just secretly meet...

398
00:27:15,570 --> 00:27:18,210
Min Jun outside
of the office anyway.

399
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:25,280
Stop weaseling your way out of it
and give me a straight answer.

400
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:29,120
Say you'll leave Adele Group
and stay out of my marriage.

401
00:27:29,990 --> 00:27:31,450
Put your money where your mouth is.

402
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:37,030
If you can't, then the deal is off.

403
00:27:37,690 --> 00:27:40,630
I'll even tell the chairman
what you're really after...

404
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:42,900
to get you kicked out of Adele.

405
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,240
Come in.

406
00:28:00,150 --> 00:28:03,150
Sir, I brought the documents
for the new product launch.

407
00:28:03,220 --> 00:28:05,720
Thanks, just leave them there.

408
00:28:07,090 --> 00:28:10,390
Looks like you're waiting
for some important news.

409
00:28:10,930 --> 00:28:13,300
Yes, a very important one.

410
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:17,070
A unique gift filled with memories
is on its way.

411
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:18,500
Sorry?

412
00:28:19,570 --> 00:28:21,740
It's like we've gone back
to a time...

413
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:24,570
when we didn't have a care
in the world.

414
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:27,880
You had a time like that?

415
00:28:29,950 --> 00:28:31,080
Back in college.

416
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:35,190
Those were the simplest
and most fun times.

417
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:37,750
What about you, Chloe?

418
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:39,690
For me...

419
00:28:41,690 --> 00:28:43,930
I think it was back then as well.

420
00:28:47,230 --> 00:28:48,870
I didn't have a care in the world...

421
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:53,900
and was just happy.

422
00:28:57,940 --> 00:29:01,410
I dug this up
by scouring social media.

423
00:29:02,950 --> 00:29:04,050
It's about Chloe.

424
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:06,320
While she was
at Helion Design School,

425
00:29:06,820 --> 00:29:08,620
she apparently designed...

426
00:29:08,850 --> 00:29:12,020
and donated winter hats
for a Korean environmental group.

427
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:14,060
Really?

428
00:29:15,130 --> 00:29:18,130
But why were you looking into that?

429
00:29:18,330 --> 00:29:22,900
I posted on social media
offering a reward for that hat.

430
00:29:23,930 --> 00:29:25,840
Money really does talk.

431
00:29:26,570 --> 00:29:29,370
I found one
in just a matter of hours.

432
00:29:29,710 --> 00:29:31,210
Is that so?

433
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:33,840
But...

434
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:37,810
why are you even looking
for the hat?

435
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,520
It's here.

436
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:51,960
I didn't expect to find one
so quickly. Thank you.

437
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:55,470
I never thought I'd sell this hat
for so much.

438
00:29:56,430 --> 00:29:58,970
The price is pretty steep.
Are you sure about this?

439
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:03,310
You can't put a price
on memories, right?

440
00:30:04,740 --> 00:30:08,710
It's a gift that will remind her
of her happiest moments.

441
00:30:10,010 --> 00:30:11,480
Anyway, it was a pleasure
doing business with you.

442
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,350
Since you made the trip out here
to meet me,

443
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:16,390
I wired you money
for your travel expenses.

444
00:30:17,850 --> 00:30:18,860
Take care.

445
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:20,460
Hold on.

446
00:30:22,290 --> 00:30:25,230
I don't think that'll remind anyone
of anything good.

447
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,000
Whoever it's for,
if they know the backstory,

448
00:30:30,470 --> 00:30:33,270
it won't be a pleasant memory.

449
00:30:35,540 --> 00:30:39,080
For the Korean environmental group,
that hat is a painful reminder.

450
00:30:41,180 --> 00:30:42,180
Wait, painful?

451
00:30:43,010 --> 00:30:44,010
What are you talking about?

452
00:30:44,350 --> 00:30:47,020
The girl who designed those hats
died...

453
00:30:47,020 --> 00:30:48,280
during a conservation activity...

454
00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:51,020
on a snow-covered mountain.

455
00:30:57,590 --> 00:30:58,700
Wait.

456
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:00,900
Don't tell me her name...

457
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,470
was Chloe.

458
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:05,570
How did you know? Yes, it was.

459
00:31:51,780 --> 00:31:52,920
Who on earth are you?

460
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:55,750
Baek Jin Ju and Chloe are both dead.

461
00:31:58,090 --> 00:32:00,690
Why do you have Baek Jin Ju's face
and go by Chloe's name?

462
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:06,600
Just who the heck are you?

463
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:15,200
We...

464
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:20,540
Why don't we get married?

465
00:32:51,870 --> 00:32:54,980
(Pearl in Red)

466
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,250
Do you even love me?

467
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:57,350
Help me.

468
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:00,150
If you need me to love you,
I'll try.

469
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,350
Stay married for just one year.

470
00:33:02,350 --> 00:33:05,420
Get back what's ours,
and you'll get your divorce.

471
00:33:05,660 --> 00:33:08,190
I'm sick of begging
that jerk Park Tae Ho.

472
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:10,260
I'm going to tear it all down.

473
00:33:10,730 --> 00:33:13,830
This time,
I'm going for the jugular.

474
00:33:15,030 --> 00:33:17,030
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
